news.title: Maharashtra co-operation department against repealing MOFA, cites benefits for stand
news.para: The state housing department, headed by deputy chief minister Devendra Fadnavis, had sought the cooperation department’s opinion on repealing MOFA as well as to review the draft of the new Maharashtra Transfer of Title in Real Estate Project bill, which is to replace MOFA.

news.title: Kolkata civic body to organise camps at housing complexes for mutation of flats
news.para: The KMC brass has taken the decision following requests from flat owners across the city who face harassment while trying to do mutation of their properties.

news.title: Mumbai: HC directs BMC to frame guidelines for use of cranes in highrise constructions
news.para: ​The trigger for the petition, said its senior counsel Prateek Seksaria, was death of 2 persons arising from construction being carried out by a developer of ‘Four Seasons Private Residences Phase I and II” on the adjoining plot.

news.title: Odisha cabinet nod to convert leasehold land to freehold
news.para: The government told the assembly on Friday that the cabinet has approved a waiver of Rs 1,107 crore towards conversion fee from leasehold to freehold land for residential properties over 1,717 acres.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: HRC questions Cidco's MD for inaction over Parsik Hill cutting
news.para: The HRC will take up the case next on March 27. Meanwhile, the environment department as well as Navi Mumbai Municipal Corporation (NMMC) have also been directed to submit their fresh affidavits.

news.title: Ahmedabad development body to hike development fee by 20 times
news.para: According to experts, this, coupled with increased jantri rates, will result in a hefty rise in belongings prices in Auda areas around Ahmedabad city in the coming months.

news.title: Redevelopment projects getting nixed with jantri hike imminent in Ahmedabad
news.para: Many redevelopment projects will not be able to get their plans passed by April 15. If plans are approved before April 15, developers pay for FSI according to the old jantri rates.

news.title: Con pays just Rs 600 for Rs 4.4 crore plot in Gurugram; HSVP to cancel allotment, registry
news.para: The plot of 500 square yards was sold through e-auction in 2021-22. The allottee made six transactions of Rs 100 each, while the HSVP’s plot and property management (PPM) system recorded that it received payment of Rs 4.4 crore.

news.title: Three TMT bar suppliers booked in Chennai for GST evasion of Rs 150 crore
news.para: Based on information, the intelligence team conducted simultaneous search operations at the properties of three prominent taxpayers involved in the business of supply of TMT bars on Thursday.

news.title: Sebi revokes securities market ban on eight former promoter entities of DHFL
news.para: The regulator said the investigation in the matter had been completed and thereafter it initiated quasi-judicial proceedings against Kapil Wadhawan, Dheeraj Wadhawan, Rakesh Kumar Wadhawan and Sarang Wadhawan who were the other four former promoters of DHFL (now known as Piramal Finance).

news.title: NCLT gives approval to Max Estates' bid to acquire 'Delhi One' project in Noida
news.para: "Our resolution plan for Delhi One project has been approved by the NCLT. A Committee of Creditors (CoC) had approved our plan in 2019," Max Ventures and Industries Ltd MaxVIL MD and CEO Sahil Vachani told reporters on Friday.

news.title: Adani family looks to sell 4.5% in Ambuja Cements to raise funds
news.para: These entities are looking to raise a little over Rs 3,000 crore through the proposed secondary sale. Equity amounting to 4.5% of the company may be sold by way of block deals, the people cited said.

news.title: NGT rejects PNB's plea for de-sealing of residential property used for commercial activity
news.para: ​The tribunal was hearing the bank's petition, according to which the PNB had earlier sanctioned a loan of Rs 250 crore to a person by creating an equitable mortgage of the property in Chanakya Place here, and for the realisation of the dues, it had auctioned the collateral property to another person.

news.title: CPM state secretary assures houses for 3.4 lakh landless people in Kerala
news.para: The government will find 15,000 acres for these landless. For the 1.5 lakh people who have land but no houses, the government would provide houses through various welfare schemes.

news.title: Seven entities in race to acquire Asian Hotels (West)
news.para: The listed Asian Hotels (West), which operates Hotel Hyatt Regency near Mumbai airport, was admitted for corporate insolvency proceeding last September.
